  "description": "Map of the greater Istanbul metropolitan area (Turkiye), from Istanbul Airport on the European side to Gebze on the Asian side, spanning both continents across the Bosphorus. 1.04M+ OSM buildings (binary format), 8.15M+ commuters with demand built from TUIK (Turkish Statistical Institute) population data by district, with jobs estimated from OpenStreetMap commercial density. Realistic traffic generators: Istanbul University, Bogazici University, Istanbul Technical University, Marmara University, Galatasaray University, two international airports (Istanbul Airport and Sabiha Gokcen) with real 2024 passenger traffic figures. Protomaps basemap with water, parks and forests. Ocean depth data for the Bosphorus, Sea of Marmara and Black Sea coastline. Simulated traffic congestion on longer commutes.",
